title: Privacy Policy
content: Last Updated: Dec 2025 Hey, Welcome! Thanks for stopping by! This Privacy Policy is just here to let you know how things work around here. My website is mainly about showcasing my work, and I'm all about respecting your privacy. What Information I Collect (Hint: Not Much) Honestly, this is just a static portfolio site, so I don't actively collect any personal information. There's no account creation, no tracking cookies, and definitely no sneaky data gathering. 1. Chatbot Conversations If you send a message through the chatbot, it might be stored for caching and training purposes. So please avoid sharing any confidential info in the chat. 2. Contact Info If you reach out via email or the contact form, the info you provide is entirely up to you. I'll only use it to reply and have a conversation with you-no funny business. How I Use the Info Here's what I might do with any information I collect: - Make sure the site is running smoothly - Improve the website based on feedback you might share - Respond to your questions or feedback Sharing Your Info (Spoiler: I Don't) I don't sell, trade, or rent your personal info. If you shared something sensitive by accident, feel free to reach out, and I'll help you remove it. Security (The Internet Isn't Perfect) I'll do my best to keep any info you share safe, but let's be real-no system is foolproof. While I'll take reasonable steps to protect your info, I can't promise 100% security. Policy Updates (No Surprises) This policy is current as of Dec 2025. If I make any changes, I'll update it here, so you're always in the loop. Feel free to check back occasionally, but don't worry-I'm not making any big changes without letting you know. Got Questions? If you any questions, concerns, or just want to say hi, drop me an email at me@oscarmejiabautista.com or use the contact form. I'd love to hear from you!

title: Project: Mise
content: Project name: Mise. Full-stack Resource Planning solution centralizing inventory, order management, and projections for multi-location restaurant operations. Technologies used: Next.js, TypeScript, tRPC, PostgreSQL, Railway, CI/CD. I built Mise using Next.js, TypeScript, tRPC, PostgreSQL, Railway, CI/CD. This project demonstrates my expertise in Next.js, TypeScript, tRPC.

title: Career: CVS Health Co. (Branding Brand) - Senior Software Engineer
content: I worked at CVS Health Co. (Branding Brand) as a Senior Software Engineer from Oct 2022 to present. Architected framework-agnostic TypeScript packages to centralize core logic, enforcing Jest and documentation standards to empower external teams to ship features independently Engineered regulatory compliance workflow for pseudoephedrine purchases (ID.me) in Next.js, advocating for a unified data contract that accelerated web and mobile development Architected client-side migration strategy to consume a unified GraphQL API, designing custom adapter patterns to eliminate network waterfalls without service interruption Orchestrated third-party ad integrations with strict API contracts, implementing React logic for targeted advertising without compromising frontend performance Collaborated on next-gen tech stack with Next.js core, migrating high-traffic Product Detail Page to improve page speed and developer velocity. My role at CVS Health Co. (Branding Brand) was Senior Software Engineer. This experience contributed to my professional growth as a software engineer.

title: Career: Freelance - Full-Stack Engineer
content: I worked at Freelance as a Full-Stack Engineer from Oct 2020 to Oct 2022. My role at Freelance was Full-Stack Engineer. This experience contributed to my professional growth as a software engineer.

title: Career: Poetic - Software Developer
